HEADWORD: Parr
<hw>Parr</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Gael. & Ir.
<ets>bradan</ets> a salmon.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A young salmon in the stage when it has dark transverse bands; --
called also <altname>samlet</altname>, <altname>skegger</altname>, and
<altname>fingerling</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A young
leveret.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

